"When Virgil, by the favour of Aungustus, had recovered his pa- trimony near Mantua, and went in hope to take possession, be was in danger to be slain by Arius the centurion, to whom those lands were assigned by the emperor, in reward of his service against Brutus and Cassius. This pastoral therefore is filled with complaints of his hard usage ; and the persons introduced are, the bailiff of Virgil, Mcris, and his friend Lycidas,"